@startuml
title UC07: buildLeaderboard() — who/when/why (end-to-end)

actor "Player View" as PLAYER
actor "Admin View" as ADMIN
actor "Live View" as LIVE
participant "Backend API Router" as API
participant "buildLeaderboard()" as BL
participant "In-memory store\n(users + gameState)" as STORE
database "SQLite" as DB

note over BL
  Зачем метод нужен:
  1) собрать актуальный TOP из users
  2) пересчитать rating для участников
  3) если game finished -> отдать frozen leaderboard
end note

== During game ==
PLAYER -> API : GET /api/profile/:id
API -> BL : buildLeaderboard()
BL -> STORE : read users/gameState
alt gameState.finished = false
  BL -> STORE : recalc leaderboard\n+ mutate rating in memory
else gameState.finished = true
  BL -> STORE : return frozen leaderboard\n(excluding admin users)
end
API -> DB : persistStore()  (current code)
API --> PLAYER : profile + gameState

ADMIN -> API : GET /api/leaderboard
API -> BL : buildLeaderboard()
BL -> STORE : read/mutate ratings
API -> DB : persistStore()  (current code)
API --> ADMIN : leaderboard + users + config

LIVE -> API : GET /api/live-leaderboard
API -> BL : buildLeaderboard()
BL -> STORE : read/mutate ratings
API -> DB : persistStore()  (current code)
API --> LIVE : public leaderboard snapshot

== Finish game ==
ADMIN -> API : POST /api/admin/finish-game
API -> STORE : buildLeaderboardEntries()\napplyRatingsFromLeaderboard()
API -> STORE : freeze leaderboard\nset finished=true
API -> DB : persistStore()
API --> ADMIN : winner + finished state

note over API,DB
  Сейчас write happens even on GET endpoints,
  потому что buildLeaderboard() имеет side-effect
  (rating mutation), и это затем сохраняется.
end note

@enduml

